VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Production site origin for Supabase auth emails (password reset redirectTo). Set on Vercel to your live origin, no trailing slash:
# VITE_SITE_URL=https://tradesman-us.vercel.app
# Also in Supabase → Authentication → URL configuration: add to Redirect URLs:
#   https://tradesman-us.vercel.app/reset-password
# If the email link opens the homepage with #...type=recovery, the app rewrites to /reset-password on load; VITE_SITE_URL still
# helps resetPasswordForEmail() send the correct redirect target.

# Optional: cross-domain legal links (defaults are /privacy, /terms, /sms-consent, /account-deletion on same host).
# Example when SMS consent is only on Vercel and privacy/terms on www.tradesman-us.com:
# VITE_PUBLIC_PRIVACY_URL=https://www.tradesman-us.com/privacy
# VITE_PUBLIC_TERMS_URL=https://www.tradesman-us.com/terms
# VITE_PUBLIC_SMS_CONSENT_URL=https://tradesman.vercel.app/sms-consent
# Google Play “Delete account URL” — default is /account-deletion on this app; override if hosted elsewhere:
# VITE_PUBLIC_ACCOUNT_DELETION_URL=https://tradesman-us.vercel.app/account-deletion

# Optional: sidebar + Account “Help Desk” display (defaults: (844) 844-1611 / +18448441611)
# VITE_HELP_DESK_PHONE_DISPLAY=(844) 844-1611
# VITE_HELP_DESK_PHONE_E164=+18448441611

# --- Vercel / serverless (set in Vercel → Project → Environment Variables) ---
# Copy from Supabase Project Settings → API (same project as VITE_*).
# Serverless /api/* routes do NOT read the Vite bundle; set these explicitly for Production (and Preview if you use it):
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<same value as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY>
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<service_role secret — never expose to the browser>
#
# Required for: Twilio webhooks (help desk, voicemail greeting save, trouble tickets), help desk greeting save, storage uploads.
# Admin trouble-ticket recording playback (/api/twilio-recording): SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (or VITE_*), or SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY if anon is not on serverless.
#
# Help desk: record MAIN opening greeting by phone (menu action "Main help desk greeting"):
# HELP_DESK_GREETING_RECORD_PIN=123456   (digits only, 4–12 chars; you enter this on the phone before recording)
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
# RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=Tradesman <onboarding@your-verified-domain.com>
# Email verified signup ping to ops (POST /api/notify-admin-verified-signup). Defaults to admin@tradesman-us.com if unset:
# ADMIN_SIGNUP_NOTIFY_EMAIL=admin@tradesman-us.com
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=...
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=...
# Optional SMS fallback if no DB channel: TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=+1...
# Optional custom SMS bridge: SMS_OUTBOUND_WEBHOOK_URL=https://...

# Optional Helcim pay portal: set ONCE on Vite build (Vercel / local .env / Capacitor) — NOT Supabase secrets.
# Recommended hands-off setup: this URL for everyone + per-user Helcim customer codes in profiles.metadata (Admin → Billing & Helcim).
# Per-user helcim_pay_portal_url in metadata is only needed as an override. App may append ?customerCode=… (confirm with Helcim).
# VITE_HELCIM_PAYMENT_PORTAL_URL=https://pay.helcim.com/v2/pay/...

# Optional Helcim.js (embedded checkout on Payments tab — see https://devdocs.helcim.com/docs/html-form-structure)
# Helcim → Integrations → Helcim.js → configuration token (public in the browser bundle).
# VITE_HELCIM_JS_TOKEN=your-helcim-js-configuration-token
# Helcim.js posts to /api/helcim-js-return on the **same origin as the page** (custom domain, www, etc.). Leave this unset unless
# you truly load the SPA from one host and must POST to another (rare). A wrong value breaks checkout on production while Vercel preview still works.
# VITE_PUBLIC_APP_ORIGIN=https://your-app.vercel.app

# --- Supabase Edge Functions (same names; set in Dashboard or CLI, not in this file) ---
# Dashboard: Project Settings → Edge Functions → Manage secrets
# CLI: supabase secrets set TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=AC... TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=...
# Use LIVE credentials for production (same as Vercel). See supabase/TWILIO_SECRETS.txt
#
# Mobile pipeline (push-test, notify-quote-status, notify-calendar-status FCM): paste full Firebase service account JSON as one secret:
#   supabase secrets set FCM_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON='{"type":"service_account",...}'
# Quote / calendar status email (notify-quote-status, notify-calendar-status): RESEND_API_KEY, RESEND_FROM_EMAIL on Supabase if not already set.
# Twilio bridge + SMS: TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER (E.164) required for twilio-bridge-call and SMS leg.
#
# Processor billing webhook — path must NOT contain vendor name in URL (their dashboard returns 400 otherwise). Deploy:
#   supabase functions deploy billing-webhook --no-verify-jwt
# Then run supabase-billing-helcim.sql. Webhook URL ends with /functions/v1/billing-webhook
# HELCIM_WEBHOOK_VERIFIER_TOKEN=<base64 verifier from Helcim → Integrations → Webhooks>
# HELCIM_API_TOKEN=<Helcim Integrations → API Access Configuration → New; any name; token must allow GET /v2/card-transactions/{id}
#   and GET /v2/customers/ (pagination). Same secret on billing-webhook, helcim-match-customers, billing-portal-config is optional.>
# Optional dev: HELCIM_INBOUND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<random> and send header x-tradesman-webhook-secret on POST
#
# Payments tab without rebuilding the Vite bundle: duplicate your hosted pay URL on Supabase so mobile/web can read it at runtime:
#   supabase secrets set HELCIM_PAYMENT_PORTAL_URL='https://...myhelcim.com/hosted/?token=...'
#   supabase functions deploy billing-portal-config
# Admin → Billing: "Match Helcim customer codes" uses Helcim API + profile emails (deploy helcim-match-customers).

# Supabase Auth (Dashboard → Authentication):
# - Site URL: your production app origin (e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app).
# - Redirect URLs: include https://your-app.vercel.app/reset-password (and http://localhost:5173/reset-password for Vite dev if needed).
# - Optional: paste branded HTML from supabase/email-templates/password-recovery.html into the Reset password template.
# For production email confirmation, configure SMTP or a provider (e.g. Resend) in Supabase → Project Settings → Auth.
